Class CommonBox<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • alex.mojaki.boxes.AbstractPowerBox<T>
      • alex.mojaki.boxes.DefaultPowerBox<T>
        • alex.mojaki.boxes.CommonBox<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Box<T>, PowerBox<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    View, WrapperBox

    public class CommonBox<T>
extends DefaultPowerBox<T>
    The simplest concrete implementation of PowerBox. You can also create one using Boxes.box(BoxFamily) or Boxes.box(Class, String).

    If you're willing to add some boilerplate to your code to save memory, see the parent DefaultPowerBox.
